olive oil
1 packet Pea Pods
1 tomato
½ lemon
2 packet beef mince
1 sachet chermoula spice blend
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
1 egg
1 tsp honey
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt

• Trim pea pods and halve lengthways.
• Cut tomato into thin wedges.
• Zest lemon to get a pinch and slice into wedges.
• In a large bowl, combine beef mince, chermoula spice blend, fine breadcrumbs and the egg.

• Using damp hands, roll beef mixture into koftas about 8cm long and 2.5cm thick.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook koftas, turning regularly, until browned and cooked through, 10-12 minutes (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).
• Remove pan from heat, add the honey and turn to coat.

• Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine mixed salad leaves, pea pods, tomato, a generous squeeze of lemon juice and a drizzle of olive oil. Season to taste.
• In a small bowl, combine Greek-style yoghurt and lemon zest.

• Divide pea pod salad between bowls.
• Top with Middle Eastern beef koftas.
• Dollop over lemon yoghurt. Enjoy!